# Create Files of Specific Size in Linux

fallocate [-o offset] -l length [-n] filename
fallocate -l 10MB my_big_file   # create a 10MB file 

KB 	KiB or K
MB 	MiB or M  # An MB (Mega Byte) is 1000*1000 bytes where as MiB (Mebibyte) is 1024*1024 bytes.
GB 	GiB or G
TB 	TiB or T
PB 	PiB or P
ZB 	ZiB or Z
YB 	YiB or Y

it also can be done with dd command
